Enumeration.Name: SyncMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: ToolTip
Enumeration.Description: The Tau camera provides the ability to either accept or output a frame synchronization signal. This functionality can also be disabled.

EnumEntry.Name: Disabled
EnumEntry.Description: The camera will turn off frame synchronization

EnumEntry.Name: SelfSyncMaster
EnumEntry.Description: The camera will output a frame synchronization signal on the Sync output pin of the GPIO connector when configured as a Sync master.

EnumEntry.Name: SelfSyncSlave
EnumEntry.Description: The camera will accept a frame synchronization signal on the Sync input signal on the GPIO connector. The camera output will be frozen if the camera is in slave mode and no external synchronization signal is received.

EnumEntry.Name: ExtSyncMaster
EnumEntry.Description: The camera will accept a frame synchronization signal on the Sync input signal on the GPIO connector. The camera output will be frozen if the camera is in slave mode and no external synchronization signal is received. The camera will output a frame synchronization signal on the Sync output pin of the GPIO connector when configured as a Sync master.

Enumeration.Description: Selects the feature User Set to load, save or configure.

Command.Description: Loads the User Set specified by UserSetSelector to the device and makes it active.

Command.Name: UserSetSave
Command.ToolTip: Save the User Set specified by UserSetSelector to the non-volatile memory of the device.
Command.Description: Save the User Set specified by UserSetSelector to the non-volatile memory of the device.

Enumeration.Name: UserSetDefaultSelector

Category.Name: Rescaler0
Category.ToolTip: Category that contains the rescaler features.
Category.Description: Category that contains the rescaler features.

Enumeration.Name: PLC_rsl0_Granularity
Enumeration.ToolTip: Controls the duration between samples, measured in system clock cycles (~30 ns).
Enumeration.Description: Controls the duration between samples, measured in system clock cycles (~30 ns).

Enumeration.Name: PLC_rsl0_Multiplier
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets the multiplier controlling the frequency of the rescaler output signal.
Enumeration.Description: Sets the multiplier controlling the frequency of the rescaler output signal.

Integer.Name: PLC_rsl0_Divider
Integer.ToolTip: Sets the divisor controlling the frequency of the rescaler output signal.
Integer.Description: Sets the divisor controlling the frequency of the rescaler output signal.

Enumeration.Name: PLC_rsl0_InputSignal
Enumeration.ToolTip: Selects the signal to be rescaled.
Enumeration.Description: Selects the signal to be rescaled.

Boolean.Name: PLC_rsl0_BackupEnabled
Boolean.ToolTip: Controls whether the rescaler switches to the backup input signal if the input signal stops.
Boolean.Description: Controls whether the rescaler switches to the backup input signal if the input signal stops. The backup input signal is not rescaled.

Integer.Name: PLC_rsl0_BackupSwitchoverDelay
Integer.ToolTip: Controls the duration of the delay to switchover, in increments of ~480 ns.
Integer.Description: Controls the duration of the delay to switchover, in increments of ~480 ns. If the rescaler detects no rising edge transition of the input signal during this switchover delay, it switches to the backup signal. When a rising edge transition is detected on the input signal, the rescaler switches back to the input signal.

Enumeration.Name: PLC_rsl0_BackupInputSignal
Enumeration.ToolTip: Selects the replacement signal if the input signal stops.
Enumeration.Description: Selects the replacement signal if the input signal stops.

Float.Name: PLC_rsl0_InputFrequency
Float.ToolTip: Returns the frequency, in Hertz, of the selected input signal.
Float.Description: Returns the frequency, in Hertz, of the selected input signal.

Float.Name: PLC_rsl0_OutputFrequency
Float.ToolTip: Returns the frequency, in Hertz, of the output from the rescaler.
Float.Description: Returns the frequency, in Hertz, of the output from the rescaler.

Enumeration.Name: PLC_rsl0_SampleSize
Enumeration.ToolTip: Returns the size of the sampling counter that is evaluating the frequency of the input signal.
Enumeration.Description: Returns the size of the sampling counter that is evaluating the frequency of the input signal.

Category.Name: Delayer0
Category.ToolTip: Category that contains the delayer features.
Category.Description: Category that contains the delayer features.

Integer.Name: PLC_del0_DelayCount
Integer.ToolTip: Controls the amount of time by which the delayer output signal will be delayed from the input signal.
Integer.Description: Controls the amount of time by which the delayer output signal will be delayed from the input signal. This delay is measured in number of periods of the reference signal.

Enumeration.Name: PLC_del0_ReferenceTimingSignal
Enumeration.ToolTip: Selects the reference signal that measures how much to delay the input signal.
Enumeration.Description: Selects the reference signal that measures how much to delay the input signal. The period of the reference signal determines both the rate at which the delayer samples the input and the duration of a delay count of 1.

Enumeration.Name: PLC_del0_InputSignal
Enumeration.ToolTip: Selects the signal to be delayed.
Enumeration.Description: Selects the signal to be delayed.

Category.Name: CounterTriggerGenerator
Category.ToolTip: Category that contains the counter trigger generator features.
Category.Description: Category that contains the counter trigger generator features.

Enumeration.Name: PLC_ts_trig_CounterSelect
Enumeration.ToolTip: Selects the source counter for the counter trigger generator.
Enumeration.Description: Selects the source counter for the counter trigger generator. Before changing the counter, ensure the trigger list is empty (PLC_ts_trig_FIFOEmpty).

Boolean.Name: PLC_ts_trig0_Enable
Boolean.ToolTip: Controls whether the PLC_ts_trig0 signal is asserted when the trigger occurs.
Boolean.Description: Controls whether the PLC_ts_trig0 signal is asserted when the trigger occurs.

Boolean.Name: PLC_ts_trig1_Enable
Boolean.ToolTip: Controls whether the PLC_ts_trig1 signal is asserted when the trigger occurs.
Boolean.Description: Controls whether the PLC_ts_trig1 signal is asserted when the trigger occurs.

Boolean.Name: PLC_ts_trig2_Enable
Boolean.ToolTip: Controls whether the PLC_ts_trig2 signal is asserted when the trigger occurs.
Boolean.Description: Controls whether the PLC_ts_trig2 signal is asserted when the trigger occurs.

Boolean.Name: PLC_ts_trig3_Enable
Boolean.ToolTip: Controls whether the PLC_ts_trig3 signal is asserted when the trigger occurs.
Boolean.Description: Controls whether the PLC_ts_trig3 signal is asserted when the trigger occurs.

Integer.Name: PLC_ts_trig_Time
Integer.ToolTip: Sets the value of the counter when the trigger is to occur.
Integer.Description: Sets the value of the counter when the trigger is to occur.

Command.Name: PLC_ts_trig_Arm
Command.ToolTip: Registers a trigger request in the queue.
Command.Description: Registers a trigger request in the queue. A trigger request is defined by a 4-bit value (defined by the PLC_ts_trig*_Enable features) outputted by the counter trigger generator when the source counter reaches a given value (defined by PLC_ts_trig_Time).

Boolean.Name: PLC_ts_trig_FIFOFull
Boolean.ToolTip: Reports whether the trigger request queue is full.

Category.Description: Category that contains acquisition configuration features.

Integer.Name: GrbCh0TrigCfgFrameToSkip
Integer.ToolTip: Controls the number of frames to skip between successively acquired frames.
Integer.Description: Controls the number of frames to skip between successively acquired frames. A value of 0 sends all frames. A value of 1 sends one frame and discards one. A value of 2 sends one frame and discards two, etc.

Enumeration.Name: GrbCh0TrigCfgContinuousPipeCount
Enumeration.ToolTip: Controls the number of GigE Vision blocks (frames) that can be in the acquisition and transfer pipe.
Enumeration.Description: Controls the number of GigE Vision blocks (frames) that can be in the acquisition and transfer pipe. A frame is considered to be in the pipe from the moment it starts until its last packet is transmitted on the Ethernet link. When the specified number of frames is reached, the IP engine ignores any new frames from the camera head until the number of frames in the pipe decreases. In continuous pipe count or recording acquisition modes, the limit is set by the amount of onboard memory available in the IP engine, rather than the number of frames in the pipe. The IP engine acquires frames from the camera until the memory is filled up to the water-level setting (GrbCh0AcqCfgMemoryWaterLevel).

Boolean.Name: GrbCh0TrigCfgAutomaticInternalRetrigger
Boolean.ToolTip: Determines whether the IP engine is automatically retrigged when FVAL stays high and the IP engine has completed the current acquisition.
Boolean.Description: Determines whether the IP engine is automatically retrigged when FVAL stays high and the IP engine has completed the current acquisition. When this feature is disabled, the IP engine waits for the next rising edge of FVAL to acquire another image.

Boolean.Name: GrbCh0TrigCfgPLCTriggerable
Boolean.ToolTip: Determines whether the PLC Q14 output is used to trigger the acquisition of a frame.
Boolean.Description: Determines whether the PLC Q14 output is used to trigger the acquisition of a frame. When enabled, this is the IP engine that is triggered, not the camera head.
